  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Abraham Lincoln
Lived:         1809 - 1865
Nationality:   American
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Emancipation Proclamation
Contribution:  16th US President; preserved Union; abolished slavery; Gettysburg Address
Quote:         "Government of the people, by the people, for the people."

Name:          Nelson Mandela
Lived:         1918 - 2013
Nationality:   South African
Field:         Politics
Known For:     End of apartheid
Contribution:  First democratically elected SA president; 27 years in prison; Nobel Peace Prize
Quote:         "Education is the most powerful weapon you can use to change the world."

Name:          Marie Curie
Lived:         1867 - 1934
Nationality:   Polish-French
Field:         Chemistry/Physics
Known For:     Radioactivity
Contribution:  First woman Nobel laureate; Nobel in two sciences; discovered radium and polonium
Quote:         "Nothing in life is to be feared, only to be understood."

